 other place . No Senator or Representative shall , during the time for which he was elected , be appointed to any civil office under the authority of the United States , which shall have been created , or the emoluments whereof shall have been increased during such time : and no person holding any office under the United States , shall be a member of either House during his continuance in office .	0
Even if facts increasing punishment beyond the maximum authorized by a guilty verdict standing alone ordinarily must be found by a jury , Arizona further urges , aggravating circumstances necessary to trigger a death sentence may nonetheless be reserved for judicial determination . As Arizonas counsel maintained at oral argument , there is no doubt that [d]eath is different. Tr . of Oral Arg . 43 . States have constructed elaborate sentencing procedures in death cases , Arizona emphasizes , because of constraints we have said the Eighth Amendment places on capital sentencing . Brief for Respondent 2125 ( citing Furman v. Georgia , 408 U. S. 238 ( 1972 ) ( per curiam ) ) ; see also Maynard v. Cartwright , 486 U. S. 356 , 362 ( 1988 ) ( Since Furman , our cases have insisted that the channeling and limiting of the sentencers discretion in imposing the death penalty is a fundamental constitutional requirement for sufficiently minimizing the risk of wholly arbitrary and capricious action. ) ; Apprendi , 530 U. S. , at 522523 ( Thomas , J. , concurring ) ( [I]n the area of capital punishment , unlike any other area , we have imposed special constraints on a legislatures ability to determine what facts shall lead to what punishmentwe have restricted the legislatures ability to define crimes. ) .	The powers not delegated to the United States by the Constitution , nor prohibited by it to the states , are reserved to the states respectively , or to the people .	0
