 of the United States . The Senate shall have the sole power to try all impeachments . When sitting for that purpose , they shall be on oath or affirmation . When the President of the United States is tried , the Chief Justice shall preside : And no person shall be convicted without the concurrence of two thirds of the members present . Judgment in cases of impeachment shall not extend further than to removal from office , and disqualification to hold and enjoy any office of honor , trust or profit under the United States : but the party convicted shall nevertheless be liable and subject to indictment , trial , judgment and punishment , according to law .	0
