Apart from the Eighth Amendment provenance of aggravating factors , Arizona presents no specific reason for excepting capital defendants from the constitutional protections … extend[ed ] to defendants generally , and none is readily apparent. Id. , at 539 ( OConnor , J. , dissenting ) . The notion that the Eighth Amendments restriction on a state legislatures ability to define capital crimes should be compensated for by permitting States more leeway under the Fifth and Sixth Amendments in proving an aggravating fact necessary to a capital sentence … is without precedent in our constitutional jurisprudence. Ibid .	The President , Vice President and all civil officers of the United States , shall be removed from office on impeachment for , and conviction of , treason , bribery , or other high crimes and misdemeanors .	0
