tate . No preference shall be given by any regulation of commerce or revenue to the ports of one state over those of another : nor shall vessels bound to , or from , one state , be obliged to enter , clear or pay duties in another . No money shall be drawn from the treasury , but in consequence of appropriations made by law ; and a regular statement and account of receipts and expenditures of all public money shall be published from time to time . No title of nobility shall be granted by the United States : and no person holding any office of profit or trust under them , shall , without the consent of the Congress , accept of any present , emolument , office , or title , of any kind whatever , from any king , prince , or foreign state .	0
