The chorus that has called for us to revisit Belton includes courts , scholars , and Members of this Court who have questioned that decisions clarity and its fidelity to Fourth Amendment principles . We therefore granted the States petition for certiorari . 552 U. S. _ _ _ ( 2008 ) .	Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion , or prohibiting the free exercise thereof ; or abridging the freedom of speech , or of the press ; or the right of the people peaceably to assemble , and to petition the government for a redress of grievances .	0
